"     The line tool draws straight lines. Select it by  pressing F9. To use it,put the cursor where you want one end of your line to be (using the SpecialCursor Control keys described in `Instructions' and `Controls'--left shift,""right shift, Alt and Ctrl), press the Insert key, release, move the cursor towhere you want the other end to be, and press Insert again. You may then, ifyou wish, adjust the line by dragging one end or the other. To do so, move the""cursor near the end of the line and press down the Insert key; the end of theline will move towards the cursor.  When you are satisfied, press F9 again. Theline will become solid and you will be free to start another one if you wish.""You can have up to twenty lines on the screen at once.                             (End of Line Tool Help)"